## Activation Protocol

<!-- WHY: Systems often require a boot sequence — components must initialize in order. -->
<!-- WHY: Without an explicit activation protocol, users invoke in wrong order and components break. -->

When the system is invoked via `{{ENTRY_POINT}}`:

1. **Boot check** — Verify all required components are present (see Component Inventory)
2. **Context load** — Read shared knowledge base from `references/`
3. **Intent detection** — Parse user input against routing table
4. **Component activation** — Activate only the components required by the detected intent
5. **State handoff** — Pass context between components using the defined data contracts
6. **Output delivery** — Route final output through `{{OUTPUT_COMPONENT}}`

If any boot check fails, surface the missing component and halt — do not attempt partial execution.

