## When NOT to Use

<!-- WHY: D14 requires explicit degradation paths. Systems are the highest-complexity product type — -->
<!-- WHY: creators must know when this form is overkill so they choose the right product type. -->

- When a single skill or agent covers the use case — composition overhead is real cost
- When components don't share state or knowledge — use independent products instead
- When the routing logic is a single if/else — a skill with branching is simpler and faster
- When no component requires another component's output — this is a bundle, not a system
- When the creator cannot maintain all components — a system with stale components is worse than no system
